==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hyomandibular
<hw>Hy`o*man*dib"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hyo-</ets> + <ets>mandibular</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining both to the hyoidean arch and the mandible or lower jaw;
<as>as, the <ex>hyomandibular</ex> bone or cartilage, a segment of the
hyoid arch which connects the lower jaw with the skull in
fishes</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The hyomandibular bone or
cartilage.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyomental</ent>⟦br⟧
